news.title: Property tax amnesty scheme for residents living in Lal Dora, other areas: NDMC
news.para: The NDMC has rolled out a new amnesty scheme in order to provide relief to the residents living in areas falling within Lal Dora, extended Lal Dora, extended 'abadi' of village and 544 unauthorised regularised colonies and unauthorised colonies and properties allotted to the Kashmiri migrants, officials said.

news.title: Mutation doesn't give property ownership right: Supreme Court
news.para: A bench of Justices M R Shah and Aniruddha Bose said an entry in revenue records does not confer title on a person whose name appears in record-of-rights.

news.title: LIC Housing raises over Rs 2,335 crore by issuing preference shares to LIC
news.para: The company has allotted 4,54,00,000 equity shares on a preferential basis to Life Insurance Corporation of India (LIC), the housing finance firm said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: About 18,000 Amrapali flat owners have 15 days to stake claim
news.para: To resolve the issues of the buyers who had purchased flats in the projects floated by the real estate company in Noida and Greater Noida, the Supreme Court had appointed a court receiver.

news.title: SIT visits Supertech Emerald Court to gather details
news.para: The group spent 20 minutes at Aster 2 – the building closest to the twin towers and most affected by their construction – to speak to some of its residents.

news.title: China Evergrande bonds rebound as loan payment extensions ease default worries
news.para: CITIC dispatched a small team to Shenzhen, where Evergrande is based, last week, but it is not optimistic that Evergrande's liquidity will improve soon, the source added, citing difficulties in finding buyers for its assets and the country's strict mortgage policies.

news.title: Apartment prices in Greece rise 4.6% in Q2 2021
news.para: Property accounts for a big chunk of household wealth in Greece, where the home ownership rate is about 73.5%, above the euro zone average of 66%, according to European Union statistics on income and living conditions.

news.title: Submit plan to utilise 25-acre vacant land in Chandigarh sectors 52 & 56: Adviser
news.para: During a meeting on Wednesday, sources revealed that urban planning department proposed to develop commercial area and green cover on the land.

news.title: LEDs to replace 54,000 sodium-based street lights in Greater Noida
news.para: ​The Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) had floated a tender for replacement of the 54,000 high-pressure sodium bulbs on street lights and private firm Surya Roshni has won the contract for the project, the officials said.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board forms committee for need-based changes
news.para: The decision was taken in the board of directors meeting of CHB under the chairmanship of UT adviser Dharam Pal, who is also chairman of CHB. However, there is no immediate relief for allottees.

news.title: Pune civic body eyes arbitration to end legal battles, mop up revenue
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) has taken up 10 cases of property tax disputes, pending in courts for 8-10 years, for disposing of through arbitration and generate Rs35-crore revenue.

news.title: Nagpur Improvement Trust terms building plans passed by NMC as illegal
news.para: “If NIT terms NMC sanctioned layouts and building plans in Gunthewari layout illegal, the civic body will initiate legal action against it,” the civic chief told the House after BJP corporator Vijay Zalke raised the issue that infighting between NIT and NMC is causing problems for thousands of landowners in Gunthewari layouts.

news.title: Nagpur: HC takes up issue of public lands being encroached, regularized
news.para: Pointing out various orders passed by the HC, the bench said all those broadly point towards illegalities of grave nature committed by Nagpur Municipal Corporation (NMC) and Nagpur Improvement Trust (NIT) officials.

news.title: South Delhi civic body launches system for real-time project tracking
news.para: South Delhi Mayor Mukesh Suryan, while introducing the system on Wednesday, along with Municipal Commissioner Gyanesh Bharti said 'PRICE' will lead to preparation of estimates of buildings in an efficient and transparent manner.

news.title: Nashik: Tehsildars get powers to issue NA permits to identified land parcels
news.para: Nashik district collector Suraj Mandhare said, “We are now granting these rights to tehsildars to provide the NA permits to land parcels that have already been marked as residential areas in the development plan.”
